The paper deals with shortest paths and their distances in a Euclidean space, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in both computational geometry and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of neighborhood graphs is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses curvature-constrained shortest paths, which is a topic in both computational geometry and scientific computing (cs.SI).
